The Financial review contains certain financial  performance measures, that are not defined by  IFRS, that are used by management to assess the  financial and operational performance of the Group.  They include among others:

 – Organic growth, Real internal growth   and Pricing;

 – Underlying trading operating profit margin   and Trading operating profit margin;

 – Net financial debt;

 – Free cash flow; and

 – Underlying earnings per share (EPS) and EPS   in constant currency. Management believes that these non‑IFRS financial  performance measures provide useful information  regarding the Group’s financial and operating  performance.
